description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a dynamic and forward thinking Emergency Department, we are committed to providing excellent leadership to our nursing team. We have a 1 year fixed term vacancy for a highly experienced Senior Sister/ Charge Nurse with the possibility of this being extended. The successful candidate will be able to demonstrate their expert knowledge of emergency nursing and be able to translate this into effective nursing practice. They will need to have proven leadership skills, be energetic, hardworking and proactive, as well as committed to their own professional development and that of others.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a Senior Sister/Charge Nurse you will be ambitious, highly motivated with excellent organizational skills. In return, we offer developmental opportunities for nursing staff interested in progressing their nursing knowledge and managerial skills&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview date: 24th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working Hours: 37.5 hours per week&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maeve Clarke, Matron Emergency Services on email: maeve.clarke@nhs.net or phone: 0208-510-7128&lt;/p&gt;
